(189, 1, '2016-08-04 19:58:40', '2016-08-04 19:58:40', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]OUR PEOPLE[/vc_column_text][vc_text_separator title="Directors" title_align="separator_align_right" align="align_right" color="custom" border_width="3" accent_color="#ac9072"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1470385961886{background-color: #4f625e !important;}"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="3/4"][vc_custom_heading text="VERNON CRESSWELL" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:left|color:%23ac9072"][vc_separator color="custom" border_width="2" accent_color="#ac9072"][vc_column_text]Director[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="234" el_class="sandileicon"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="3/4"][vc_column_text]Vernon has a long-standing and proven track record in the Wealth Management industry in South Africa. He and a few colleagues built up a very successful bespoke Financial Planning business, which they later sold to a listed financial services company. After serving out a restraint, Vernon was headhunted by Standard Bank to start up their Private Bank. After successfully completing this assignment, he was appointed Head of the Bank''s Wealth division - concentrating on the Group''s Private Banking, Private Client, Asset Management and Insurance businesses. Before joining SP Wealth he was responsible for the Bank''s Wealth business across the African continent.\n\nHe has a deep understanding of Investment and Retirement planning and the critical role SP Wealth plays in this space. He is a firm believer in the independent advisory model and the need to provide a holistic offering to clients where on-going advice and service is critical.\n\nVernon also enjoys spending time with his family - often in the bush.\n\nHis qualifications include:\n\n• B Comm LLB - Rhodes University\n• H Dip Tax Law - University of Johannesburg (Wits)\n• H Dip Company Law - University of Johannesburg (Wits)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1470385961886{background-color: #4f625e !important;}"][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="3/4"][vc_custom_heading text="KATH FABER" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:left|color:%23ac9072"][vc_separator color="custom" border_width="3" accent_color="#ac9072"][vc_column_text]Financial Planner[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="238" el_class="sandileicon"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="3/4"][vc_column_text]Kath Faber has 13 years’ experience in the wealth management industry. Her career experience includes nine years as a wealth advisor for Standard Bank Private Clients where she provided a comprehensive and bespoke service to a portfolio of high net worth clients. Prior to that, Kath held a position as financial planner with Alexander Forbes Financial Services which gave her valuable insight into the Employee Benefits industry. Kath has extensive experience in providing a holistic solution to clients including investment, retirement and fiduciary advice.\n\nHer qualifications include:\n\n• B Comm, Business Finance and Economics - University of Natal, PMB\n• Honours Economics - University of Natal, PMB\n• Post Graduate Diploma in Financial Planning - University of the Free State\n• Certified Financial Planner (CFP)\n• Completion of RE1 Examinations[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Our People', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'our-people', '', '', '2016-08-05 09:52:13', '2016-08-05 09:52:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/luke/?page_id=189', 0, 'page', '', 0),
